== \"UNIT_PET\" then\n        \n        if not unit then return end\n        \n        -- Only accept raid units\n        if unit:sub(1,4) ~= \"raid\" then return end\n        \n        -- Get pet print(format(\"[%s] Removing %s (%s) on %s\",\n                    e,\n                    pet_owner_guid,aura_env.tbl_pets_on_kineticbomb[pet_owner_guid].owner,\n == UnitGUID(\"mouseover\") and as[\"\"] then\n                as[\"\"].stacks = as[\"\"].stacks - 1\n                as[\"\"].changed = true\n                \n                -- Update state table with additional information if pet was mine\n                if pet_owner_guid == UnitGUID(\"player\") then\n                    as[\"\"].my_pet_on_this_target = false\n                end\n                return true\n            end\n        end\n    elseif e == \"ENCOUNTER_START\" or e== \"ENCOUNTER_END\" or e == \"PLAYER_ENTERING_WORLD\" then\n        aura_env.tbl_pets_on_kineticbomb = {}\n        for _, state in pairs(as) do\n            state.changed = true\n            state.show = false\n        end\n        return true\n    elseif e == \"OPTIONS\" or e == \"STATUS\" then\n        for _, state in pairs(as) do\n            state.changed = true\n            state.show = false\n        end\n        return true\n    elseif e == \"UPDATE_MOUSEOVER_UNIT\" or e == \"CURSOR_CHANGED\" or e == \"WORLD_CURSOR_TOOLTIP_UPDATE\" then\n        -- The only reason the 2 cursor events are here is because retail's UPDATE_MOUSE_UNIT doesn't update when\n        -- you transition from a mouseover'd unit to no unit, which means I cannot untrigger the weakaura (on retail, for testing)\n        \n        if aura_env.ts_last_triggered == GetTime() then return end\n        aura_env.ts_last_triggered = GetTime()\n        C_Timer.After(0, function()\n                WeakAuras.ScanEvents(\"PixolICCBloodPrinceKineticBombMouseoverEvent\")\n        end)\n    elseif e == \"PixolICCBloodPrinceKineticBombMouseoverEvent\" then\n        local unit_guid = UnitGUID(\"mouseover\")\n        \n        -- Kinetic Bomb npcID\n        if (not unit_guid) or true\n                end\n            end\n        end\n        \n        -- Scan for Kinetic Bomb Unstable Buff that tells how long until it will dissipate\n        -- Alternate method is check its aura_env.text2 = \"Haste +30%\"\nend\n\naura_env.blank = function(a, aid)\n    a[aid] = {\n        show = true,\n        changed = true,\n    }\nend\n\naura_env.off = function(a, aid)\n    a[aid] = {\n        show = false,\n    }\nend\n\naura_env.tblTargetConfig = {\n    [\"37813\"] = {scanLimit = 1, inactivitySecondsThreshold = 1}, -- target\n}\n\n-- Determines if all units have been found based on config settings\naura_env.doneScanning = nil\naura_env.isDoneScanning = function()\n    for _,v in pairs(aura_env.tblTargetConfig) do\n        if (not v.scanCnt) or (v.scanCnt == 0) or (v.scanCnt ~= v.scanLimit) then return end\n    end\n    return true\nend\n\n-- Initial some variables for scan counts\nfor _,targetConfig in pairs(aura_env.tblTargetConfig) do\n    targetConfig.scanCnt = 0\nend\n\n-- Update allstates table for a specific unit\naura_env.updateTarget = function(as, unit)\n    if not unit then return end\n    \n    local guid = UnitGUID(unit)\n    if not guid then return end\n    \n    -- Don't run twice for the same unit (this applies only when called by scanTargets)\n    if aura_env.updatedGUIDs and aura_env.updatedGUIDs[guid] then return end\n    \n    local npcId = select(6, strsplit(\"-\", guid))\n    if not npcId then return end\n    \n    local targetConfig = aura_env.tblTargetConfig[npcId]\n    if not targetConfig then return end\n    \n    -- Keep track of how many times this npc has been scanned so far (used with scanLimit and doneScanning)\n    targetConfig.scanCnt = targetConfig.scanCnt + 1\n    \n    local value = UnitPower(unit) / UnitPowerMax(unit) * 100\n    local raidMarkIndex = GetRaidTargetIndex(unit)\n    \n    local changed_anything\n    \n    -- Only create state if health > 0 because CLEU:UNIT_DIED happens before the final UNIT_HEALTH event\n    if (value >= 0) and (not as[guid]) then\n        as[guid] = {\n            show = true,\n            changed = true,\n            progressType = \"static\",\n            value = value,\n            total = 100,\n            health = UnitPower(unit),\n            maxhealth = UnitPowerMax(unit),\n            icon = targetConfig.icon,\n            name = UnitName(unit),\n            index = targetConfig.index,\n            guid = guid,\n            npcId = npcId,\n            inactivitySecondsThreshold = targetConfig.inactivitySecondsThreshold,\n            raidMarkIndex = raidMarkIndex,\n            raidMark = raidMarkIndex and \"{rt\" .. raidMarkIndex .. \"}\",\n            dead = false,\n            autoHide = nil,\n        }\n        changed_anything = true\n    end\n    \n    if not as[guid] then return end\n    \n    -- Resolve an issue with UnitName returning \"Unknown\"\n    if not as[guid].name then\n        local name = targetConfig.name or UnitName(unit)\n        if name and (name ~= UNKNOWNOBJECT) then\n            as[guid].name = name\n            as[guid].changed = true\n            changed_anything = true\n        end\n    end\n    \n    if value ~= as[guid].value then\n        as[guid].show = value\n        as[guid].value = value\n        as[guid].health = UnitPower(unit)\n        as[guid].changed = true\n        changed_anything = true\n    end\n    \n    if raidMarkIndex ~= as[guid].raidMarkIndex then\n        as[guid].raidMarkIndex = raidMarkIndex\n        as[guid].raidMark = raidMarkIndex and \"{rt\" .. raidMarkIndex .. \"}\"\n        as[guid].changed = true\n        changed_anything = true\n    end\n    \n    as[guid].tsUpdate = GetTime()\n    \n    aura_env.doneScanning = aura_env.isDoneScanning()\n    if aura_env.updatedGUIDs then aura_env.updatedGUIDs[guid] = true end\n    return changed_anything\nend\n\n-- Update allstates table for all units found\naura_env.updatedGUIDs = nil\naura_env.scanTargets = function(as)\n    \n    local changed_anything\n    \n    -- Reset variables\n    aura_env.doneScanning = nil\n    aura_env.updatedGUIDs = {}\n    for _,targetConfig in pairs(aura_env.tblTargetConfig) do\n        targetConfig.scanCnt = 0\n    end\n    \n    -- Scan mouseover and focus\n    changed_anything = aura_env.updateTarget(as, \"mouseover\") or changed_anything\n    changed_anything = aura_env.updateTarget(as, \"focus\") or changed_anything\n    \n    -- Scan Nameplates\n    if not aura_env.doneScanning then\n        for _,v in pairs(C_NamePlate.GetNamePlates()) do\n            local unit = v.namePlateUnitToken\n            changed_anything = aura_env.updateTarget(as, unit) or changed_anything\n            if aura_env.doneScanning then break end\n        end\n    end\n    \n    -- Scan Raid+RaidPet Targets\n    if not aura_env.doneScanning then\n        for unit in WA_IterateGroupMembers() do\n            \n            -- Raid target\n            changed_anything = aura_env.updateTarget(as, unit .. \"target\") or changed_anything\n            if aura_env.doneScanning then break end\n            \n            -- Raid pet target\n            changed_anything = aura_env.updateTarget(as, unit .. \"pettarget\") or changed_anything\n            if aura_env.doneScanning then break end\n        end\n    end\n    \n    -- Hide old states that weren't updated for a while\n    for guid,state in pairs(as) do\n        if not aura_env.updatedGUIDs[guid] then\n            if as[guid].inactivitySecondsThreshold and (GetTime() - as[guid].tsUpdate) > as[guid].inactivitySecondsThreshold then\n                as[guid].show = false\n                state.changed = true\n                changed_anything = true\n            end\n        end\n    end\n    aura_env.updatedGUIDs = nil\n    return changed_anything\n    \nend",

      xOffset = 300,
      yOffset = 200
    }, {
      actions = {
        finish = {
          hide_all_glows = false
        },
        init = {
          custom = "local Details = Details  -- avoids 'accessing undefined variable' Wago code review\nlocal ADDON_PREFIX = \"WA_BQLBC_DIST\"\nlocal ESSENCE_OF_THE_BLOOD_QUEEN = {\n  [70867] = true,\n  [70871] = true,\n  [70872] = true,\n  [70879] = true,\n  [70950] = true,\n}\nlocal FRENZIED_BLOODTHIRST = 70877\nlocal UNCONTROLLABLE_FRENZY = 70923\nlocal VAMPIRES = {}  -- {\"Player-4476-04EECE8A\", \"Player-4476-04E21AF5\", ...}\nlocal DISTANCES = {}  -- {\"Player-4476-04EECE8A\": {\"Player-4476-04E21AF5\": 4, \"Player-4476-04E22185\": 20, ...}, \"Player-4476-04E21AF5\": {...}, ...}\nlocal DURATIONS = {}  -- {\"Player-4476-04EECE8A\": {expirationTime: 1337, duration: 60}, ...}\nlocal MARKS = {}  -- {\"Player-4476-04EECE8A\": 1,  \"Player-4476-04E21AF5\": 5, ...}\n\nlocal function GetConfigPriorityPlayers()\n  -- Explicitly iterate group members to avoid weirdly-named pets or mirror images\n  local nameToGuid = {}\n  for unit in WA_IterateGroupMembers() do\n    nameToGuid[strlower(UnitName(unit))] = UnitGUID(unit)\n  end\n  local priorityPlayers = {}\n  -- '%S+' matches on any non-space characters, essentially splitting on any newline, space, etc.\n  for name in gmatch(aura_env.config.priorityPlayers, \"%S+\") do\n    local guid = nameToGuid[strlower(name)]\n    if guid and not tContains(priorityPlayers, guid) then\n      tinsert(priorityPlayers, guid)\n    end\n  end\n  DebugPrint(\"PriorityPlayers\", priorityPlayers)\n  return priorityPlayers\nend\n\n\nlocal function GetBiteTargets()\n  -- Get bite targets in order of preference\n  local targets = {}\n  \n  -- Some functions do not support GUIDs but require unit IDs\n  local guidToUnit = {}\n  for unit in WA_IterateGroupMembers() do\n    guidToUnit[UnitGUID(unit)] = unit\n  end\n  \n  local function AddTarget(guid)\n    -- Bail if already a target\n    if tContains(targets, guid) then\n      return\n    end\n    -- Bail if already a vampire\n    if tContains(VAMPIRES, guid) then\n      return\n    end\n    -- Bail if unknown unit\n    local unit = guidToUnit[guid]\n    if not unit then\n      return\n    end\n    -- Bail if dead\n    if UnitIsDeadOrGhost(unit) then\n      return\n    end\n    -- Bail if disconnected\n    if not UnitIsConnected(unit) then\n      return\n    end\n    tinsert(targets, guid)\n  end\n  \n  -- Priority players from custom options\n  for _, guid in ipairs(GetConfigPriorityPlayers()) do\n    AddTarget(guid)\n  end\n  -- Players from the Details! AddOn, in order of damage done\n  -- https://github.com/Tercioo/Details-Damage-Meter/blob/master/API.txt\n  if Details then\n    local currentCombat = Details:GetCurrentCombat()\n    local damageContainer = currentCombat[1]\n    damageContainer:SortByKey(\"total_without_pet\")\n    for _, actor in damageContainer:ListActors() do\n      if actor:IsGroupPlayer() then\n        AddTarget(actor:guid())\n      end\n    end\n  else\n    print(\"[BITE COORDINATOR] WARNING: The Details! AddOn is used to find bite targets when the priority players in custom options are insufficient, but it is not installed.\")\n  end\n  \n  DebugPrint(\"BiteTargets\", targets)\n  return targets\nend\n\n\nlocal function SetRaidTargetIdempotent(unit, index)\n  -- SetRaidIndex sends a request to the server even though the mark is already applied to the target, and is thus\n  -- rate-limited if done too much. The following ensures we only send the request if necessary.\n  if GetRaidTargetIndex(unit) ~= index then\n    DebugPrint(\"SetRaidTarget\", unit, index)\n    SetRaidTarget(unit, index or 0)  -- marks are removed by setting zero, not nil\n  end\nend\n\n\nlocal function Hungarian(t)\n  -- Based on Leonid Krashenko's adaptation of Andrey Lopatin's Hungarian Algorithm\n  --local t = {\n  --  { 81, 12, 84, 18, 15, 80, 19, 53, 14, 8 },\n  --  { 37, 65, 65, 49, 53, 80, 44, 46, 21, 18 },\n  --  { 30, 73, 70, 98, 31, 46, 79, 45, 29, 16 },\n  --  { 50, 2, 71, 93, 65, 25, 43, 86, 74, 70 },\n  --  { 74, 80, 79, 93, 1, 40, 23, 15, 70, 83 },\n  --  { 10, 9, 98, 59, 13, 29, 41, 16, 78, 80 },\n  --  { 21, 71, 90, 10, 78, 56, 93, 78, 56, 75 },\n  --  { 42, 9, 44, 42, 73, 48, 53, 80, 31, 97 },\n  --  { 5, 46, 81, 75, 57, 29, 76, 59, 8, 82 },\n  --  { 91, 42, 96, 7, 78, 93, 70, 67, 92, 43 },\n  --}\n  --local a = Hungarian(t)\n  --assert(a[1] == 7)\n  --assert(a[2] == 9)\n  --assert(a[3] == 10)\n  --assert(a[4] == 2)\n  --assert(a[5] == 5)\n  --assert(a[6] == 8)\n  --assert(a[7] == 1)\n  --assert(a[8] == 3)\n  --assert(a[9] == 6)\n  --assert(a[10] == 4)\n  local n = #t + 1\n  local m = #(t[1]) + 1\n  \n  local u = {}\n  local v = {}\n  local p = {}\n  local way = {}\n  \n  for i = 1, n do\n    p[1] = i\n    local j0 = 1\n    local minv = {}\n    local used = {}\n    \n    while true do\n      used[j0] = true\n      local i0 = p[j0] or 1\n      local delta = math.huge\n      local j1\n      for j = 2, m do\n        if not used[j] then\n          local weight = (i0 == 1 or j == 1) and 0 or t[i0 - 1][j - 1]\n          local cur = weight - (u[i0] or 0) - (v[j] or 0)\n          if not minv[j] or cur < minv[j] then\n            minv[j] = cur\n            way[j] = j0\n          end\n          if minv[j] and minv[j] < delta then\n            delta = minv[j]\n            j1 = j\n          end\n        end\n      end\n      for j = 1, m do\n        if used[j] then\n          local pj = p[j] or 1\n          u[pj] = (u[pj] or 0) + delta\n          v[j] = (v[j] or 0) - delta\n        elseif minv[j] then\n          minv[j] = minv[j] - delta\n        end\n        j0 = j1\n      end\n      if (p[j0] or 1) == 1 then\n        break\n      end\n    end\n    while true do\n      local j1 = (way[j0] or 0)\n      p[j0] = p[j1] or 1\n      j0 = j1\n      if j0 == 1 then\n        break\n      end\n    end\n  end\n  -- Restore answer; i.e. find the assigned column for each row\n  local ans = {}\n  for j = 2, m do\n    ans[p[j] - 1] = j - 1\n  end\n  return ans\nend\n\n\nlocal function GetVampireTargetIndexes(targetGuids)\n  -- We can only mark as many targets as there are vampires, up to the maximum of 8 marks which exist in the game. The\n  -- boss' enrage timer, and the fact that it is a 25 player raid, ensures we will never need to bite more targets in a\n  -- single round anyway.\n  local numTargets = math.min(#VAMPIRES, #targetGuids, 8)\n  \n  -- Bail if there are no vampires to avoid breaking the Hungarian Algorithm\n  if numTargets == 0 then\n    return {}\n  end\n  \n  -- The Hungarian Algorithm takes a 2d array of vampires and their distance (cost) to each target\n  local distances = {}\n  for vampireIndex = 1, numTargets do\n    local vampireGuid = VAMPIRES[vampireIndex]\n    local vampireTargetDistances = {}\n    for targetIndex = 1, numTargets do\n      local targetGuid = targetGuids[targetIndex]\n      local distance = (DISTANCES[vampireGuid] or {})[targetGuid] or 40  -- TODO: default?\n      vampireTargetDistances[targetIndex] = distance\n    end\n    distances[vampireIndex] = vampireTargetDistances\n  end\n  \n  -- Assign vampires to targets such that the total distance is minimised\n  DebugPrint(\"distances\", distances)\n  local vampireTargetIndexes = Hungarian(distances)\n  DebugPrint(\"assigned vampireTargetIndexes\", vampireTargetIndexes)\n  return vampireTargetIndexes\nend\n\n\nlocal function ShouldAssignMarks()\n  -- Only the Raid Leader is allowed to assign marks. Having multiple people marking would certainly lead to chaos.\n  return UnitIsGroupLeader(\"player\")\nend\n\n\nlocal function IsAssignmentsLocked()\n  -- To avoid confusion, assignments are locked if anyone is currently/about to be a frenzied vampire\n  -- WARNING: These values should be kept in sync with the lock/unlock statusbar.\n  local now = GetTime()\n  for _, aura in pairs(DURATIONS) do\n    local isActive = aura.expirationTime >= now\n    local isFrenzied = aura.duration == 10\n    local isFrenziedSoon = aura.expirationTime - now <= 10\n    if isActive and (isFrenzied or isFrenziedSoon) then\n      return true\n    end\n  end\n  return false\nend\n\n\nfunction aura_env.WA_BQLBC_ASSIGN_MARKS_TICKER()\n  -- Marks are assigned using a ticker, rather than being event-driven, so they aren't accidentally spam-changed, which\n  -- would be very confusing (and rate-limit us).\n  if not ShouldAssignMarks() then\n    return false\n  end\n  -- Bail if assignments are locked, when anyone is currently/about to be a frenzied vampire\n  if IsAssignmentsLocked() then\n    return false\n  end\n  DebugPrint(\"ASSIGN_MARKS_TICKER\")\n  \n  -- Get preferred bite targets and calculate optimal vampire assignment\n  local targetGuids = GetBiteTargets()\n  local vampireTargetIndexes = GetVampireTargetIndexes(targetGuids)\n  \n  -- Assign the marks\n  wipe(MARKS)\n  for vampireIndex, targetIndex in ipairs(vampireTargetIndexes) do\n    local targetGuid = targetGuids[targetIndex]\n    MARKS[targetGuid] = vampireIndex\n  end\n  -- The target will be marked by the ENSURE MARKS ticker below. This is done separately to allow re-marking with the\n  -- same marks (in case other AddOns or WeakAuras overwrite them) more aggressively than we assign mew ones.\n  return false\nend\n\n\nfunction aura_env.WA_BQLBC_ENSURE_MARKS_TICKER(allStates)\n  -- Ensure the targets (and only the targets) are marked as assigned. This is done ~3x more often than the assignment\n  -- as a balance between getting rate-limited and overwriting potential marks from other AddOns or WeakAuras.\n  DebugPrint(\"WA_BQLBC_ENSURE_MARKS_TICKER\")\n  if not ShouldAssignMarks() then\n    return false\n  end\n  -- NOTE: We intentionally do not bail on IsAssignmentsLocked() since this does not _change_ any marks, just ensures we\n  -- overwrite potential changes from other AddOns or WeakAuras.\n  DebugPrint(\"EnsureMarks\")\n  for unit in WA_IterateGroupMembers() do\n    local guid = UnitGUID(unit)\n    local mark = MARKS[guid]\n    -- If the unit does not have a mark assigned (nil), but is currently marked, this will remove it from them\n    SetRaidTargetIdempotent(unit, mark)\n  end\n  return false\nend\n\n\nlocal function UpdateDisplay(allStates)\n  DebugPrint(\"UpdateDisplay\")\n  -- Clear all existing states\n  for _, state in pairs(allStates) do\n    state.show = false\n    state.changed = true\n  end\n  \n  -- Find all marked raid member GUIDs\n  local raidMarkToGuid = {}\n  for unit in WA_IterateGroupMembers() do\n    local index = GetRaidTargetIndex(unit)\n    if index then\n      raidMarkToGuid[index] = UnitGUID(unit)\n    end\n  end\n  \n  -- Show vampires, their raid mark, and assigned target (if any)\n  for index, guid in ipairs(VAMPIRES) do\n    -- The WA is built around raid marks, which there are only 8 of. Don't show any vampires above this number.\n    if index > 8 then\n      break\n    end\n    local destGuid = raidMarkToGuid[index]\n    local duration = DURATIONS[guid]\n    allStates[index] = {\n      show = true,\n      changed = true,\n      progressType = \"timed\",\n      expirationTime = duration.expirationTime,\n      duration = duration.duration,\n      index = -index,\n      raidTargetIndex = index,\n      sourceGuid = guid,\n      destGuid = destGuid,\n      isMe = (guid == WeakAuras.myGUID) or (destGuid == WeakAuras.myGUID),\n    }\n    -- Update auxiliary aura displays, such as circle and raid frame glow, if we are the zombie\n    if guid == WeakAuras.myGUID then\n      WeakAuras.ScanEvents(\"WA_BQLBC_MY_TARGET\", destGuid, index)\n    end\n  end\n  return true\nend\n\n\nlocal function GetEssenceOfTheBloodQueenDuration()\n  -- Essence of the Blood Queen is 75 seconds on 10-player and 60 seconds on 25-player, but has the same spell ID\n  local _, _, _, _, maxPlayers = GetInstanceInfo()\n  return maxPlayers == 10 and 75 or 60\nend\n\n\nlocal function SetDuration(guid, duration)\n  DURATIONS[guid] = {\n    expirationTime = GetTime() + duration,\n    duration = duration,\n  }\nend\n\n\nfunction aura_env.COMBAT_LOG_EVENT_UNFILTERED(allStates, _, subEvent, _, _, _, _, _, destGuid, destName, _, _, spellId)\n  if subEvent == \"SPELL_AURA_APPLIED\" and ESSENCE_OF_THE_BLOOD_QUEEN[spellId] then\n    -- Insert target into ordered table if was the first time they were bitten. Note that this is ordered consistently\n    -- raid-wide, so everyone agrees which vampire bites which raid mark. This allows everyone to know the bite\n    -- assignment without synchronisation any data other than the raid marks, which is done automatically by the game.\n    if not tContains(VAMPIRES, destGuid) then\n      DebugPrint(\"Add vampire\", destGuid)\n      tinsert(VAMPIRES, destGuid)\n    end\n    SetDuration(destGuid, GetEssenceOfTheBloodQueenDuration())\n  elseif subEvent == \"SPELL_AURA_APPLIED\" and spellId == FRENZIED_BLOODTHIRST then\n    SetDuration(destGuid, 10)\n  elseif (subEvent == \"SPELL_AURA_APPLIED\" and spellId == UNCONTROLLABLE_FRENZY) or (subEvent == \"UNIT_DIED\" and not UnitIsFeignDeath(destName)) then\n    -- Target died or got Mind-Controlled; find and remove them from VAMPIRES. Note that vampires lose and gain the\n    -- Essence of the Blood Queen debuff throughout the fight, so it cannot be used as a reliable vampire indicator.\n    for index, guid in ipairs(VAMPIRES) do\n      if guid == destGuid then\n        -- It is generally ill-advised to tremove while iterating the array - but fine if we break immediately after\n        DebugPrint(\"Remove vampire\", destGuid)\n        tremove(VAMPIRES, index)\n        break\n      end\n    end\n  else\n    return false\n  end\n  return UpdateDisplay(allStates)\nend\n\n\nfunction aura_env.RAID_TARGET_UPDATE(allStates)\n  DebugPrint(\"RAID_TARGET_UPDATE\")\n  return UpdateDisplay(allStates)\nend\n\n\nfunction aura_env.WA_BQLBC_SEND_DISTANCES_TICKER(allStates)\n  -- Calculate distance to each raid member.\n  -- AddOn messages are limited in size, so instead of sending all unit GUIDs, we rely on the fact that raid unit\n  -- indexes (raid1, raid2, ..., raidN) are consistent amongst players.\n  DebugPrint(\"WA_BQLBC_SEND_DISTANCES\")\n  local distances = {}\n  for i = 1, MAX_RAID_MEMBERS do\n    local unit = \"raid\" .. i\n    -- Although ugly type-wise, it's convenient that 'distance' is an empty string - instead of nil - when\n    -- string-joining the 'distances' table later.\n    local distance = \"\"\n    local min, max = WeakAuras.GetRange(unit)\n    if min and max then\n      distance = math.ceil((min + max) / 2)\n    end\n    distances[i] = distance\n  end\n  -- Encode and send to raid\n  local message = table.concat(distances, \",\")\n  C_ChatInfo.SendAddonMessage(ADDON_PREFIX, message, \"RAID\")\n  return false\nend\n\n\nfunction aura_env.CHAT_MSG_ADDON(allStates, prefix, text, channel, sender)\n  -- Bail if not this WeakAuras' AddOn prefix, or message (somehow) from outside the raid\n  if prefix ~= ADDON_PREFIX or channel ~= \"RAID\" then\n    return false\n  end\n  -- There is no need to process the raid members' distances if we won't be assigning marks anyway\n  if not ShouldAssignMarks() then\n    return false\n  end\n  DebugPrint(\"CHAT_MSG_ADDON\", text, sender)\n  \n  -- Decode the distance string back into a table\n  local distanceStrings = strsplittable(\",\", text)\n  local distances = {}\n  for i = 1, MAX_RAID_MEMBERS do\n    local unit = \"raid\" .. i\n    local distance = tonumber(distanceStrings[i])\n    local unitGuid = UnitGUID(unit)\n    if unitGuid and distance then\n      distances[unitGuid] = distance\n    end\n  end\n  local senderGuid = UnitGUID(Ambiguate(sender, \"short\")) -- ugly hack to convert \"Strace-Gehennas\" to GUID\n  DISTANCES[senderGuid] = distances\n  \n  -- Return false; we will update later if the raid marks change based on the new distance information\n  return false\nend\n\n\nfunction aura_env.ENCOUNTER_END(allStates)\n  -- Remove all raid marks when the fight is over, if we were the one marking\n  if not ShouldAssignMarks() then\n    return false\n  end\n  DebugPrint(\"ENCOUNTER_END: Clearing marks\")\n  for unit in WA_IterateGroupMembers() do\n    if GetRaidTargetIndex(unit) then\n      SetRaidTargetIdempotent(unit, 0)  -- 0 removes the target's mark\n    end\n  end\n  return false\nend\n\n\nfunction aura_env.STATUS(allStates)\n  -- Clear caches when the aura is initialised\n  DebugPrint(\"STATUS\")\n  wipe(VAMPIRES)\n  wipe(DISTANCES)\n  wipe(DURATIONS)\n  wipe(MARKS)\n  return false\nend\n\n\nfunction aura_env.OPTIONS(allStates)\n  -- Show fake display data when WeakAuras options is open\n  DebugPrint(\"OPTIONS\")\n  local guid = WeakAuras.myGUID\n  for i = 1, 8 do\n    VAMPIRES[i] = guid\n    SetDuration(guid, 60)\n  end\n  return UpdateDisplay(allStates)\nend\n\n-- Register the AddOn prefix so we receive CHAT_MSG_ADDON events for it\nC_ChatInfo.RegisterAddonMessagePrefix(ADDON_PREFIX)",
          do_custom = true

          do_custom = false

          custom = "local MESSAGE_PREFIX = \"WA_VERSION_CHECK\"\n\n\nlocal function defaultdict()\n  return setmetatable({}, {\n      __index = function(t, k)\n        local default = defaultdict()\n        rawset(t, k, default)\n        return default\n      end\n  })\nend\n\nlocal versions = defaultdict()\nlocal reporterAuraId = nil\n\n\nlocal function sortedSemvers(versionStrings)\n  local semvers = {}\n  for _, versionString in ipairs(versionStrings) do\n    local major, minor, patch = string.match(versionString, \"(%d+)%.(%d+)%.(%d+)\")\n    if major and minor and patch then\n      tinsert(semvers, {tonumber(major), tonumber(minor), tonumber(patch)})\n    end\n  end\n  table.sort(semvers, function (a, b)\n      for i = 1, 3 do\n        if a[i] < b[i] then return false end\n        if a[i] > b[i] then return true end\n      end\n  end)\n  for i, semver in ipairs(semvers) do\n    semvers[i] = strjoin(\".\", unpack(semver))\n  end\n  return semvers\nend\n\n\nlocal function request(auraId, channel)\n  local data = WeakAuras.GetData(auraId)\n  -- Allow overwriting reported version of a WA by setting 'semver:x.y.z' in its description\n  local version = data and ((data.desc and data.desc:match(\"semver:(%d+%.%d+%.%d+)\")) or data.semver) or \"NOT_INSTALLED\"\n  local message = strjoin(\" \", \"RESPONSE\", version, auraId)\n  C_ChatInfo.SendAddonMessage(MESSAGE_PREFIX, message, channel)\nend\n\n\nlocal function response(auraId, version, sender)\n  sender = Ambiguate(sender, \"none\")\n  versions[auraId][version][sender] = true\n  versions[auraId][\"NO_RESPONSE\"][sender] = nil\nend\n\n\nfunction aura_env.CHAT_MSG_ADDON(prefix, text, channel, sender, ...)\n  if prefix ~= MESSAGE_PREFIX then\n    return false\n  end\n  local command, message = strsplit(\" \", text, 2)\n  if command == \"REQUEST\" then\n    return request(message, channel)\n  elseif command == \"RESPONSE\" then\n    local version, auraId = strsplit(\" \", message, 2)\n    return response(auraId, version, sender)\n  end\n  return false\nend\n\n\nlocal function reportVersion(version, versionName, channel)\n  local players = {}\n  for player, _ in pairs(version) do\n    tinsert(players, Ambiguate(player, \"none\"))\n  end\n  table.sort(players)\n  if #players == 0 then\n    return\n  end\n  local message = format(\"%s: %s\", versionName, table.concat(players, \" \"))\n  SendChatMessage(message, channel)\nend\n\n\nlocal function report(auraVersions, channel)\n  -- Collect versions, in order\n  local sortedVersions = {}\n  for versionString, _ in pairs(auraVersions) do\n    tinsert(sortedVersions, versionString)\n  end\n  sortedVersions = sortedSemvers(sortedVersions)\n  -- Report semvers\n  for _, version in ipairs(sortedVersions) do\n    reportVersion(auraVersions[version], version, channel)\n  end\n  -- Report special-cases\n  reportVersion(auraVersions[\"NOT_INSTALLED\"], \"Not Installed\", channel)\n  reportVersion(auraVersions[\"NO_RESPONSE\"], \"No Response\", channel)\nend\n\n\nlocal function scheduleReport(auraId, channel)\n  WeakAuras.ScanEvents(\"WA_VERSION_CHECK_REPORT_DEDUPLICATE\", aura_env.id)\n  if reporterAuraId ~= aura_env.id then\n    return\n  end\n  versions[auraId] = nil\n  for unit in WA_IterateGroupMembers() do\n    versions[auraId][\"NO_RESPONSE\"][GetUnitName(unit,  true)] = true\n  end\n  C_Timer.After(1, function()\n      report(versions[auraId], channel)\n  end)\nend\n\n\nfunction aura_env.WA_VERSION_CHECK_REPORT_DEDUPLICATE(auraId)\n  -- Ensure we only report to chat once, even though we have multiple versions of this WA installed\n  if not reporterAuraId then\n    reporterAuraId = auraId\n  end\n  return false\nend\n\n\nlocal function chatMessage(text, guid, channel)\n  local command, auraId = strsplit(\" \", text, 2)\n  if command ~= \"!wav\" then\n    return false\n  end\n  -- Schedule report if our message\n  if guid == WeakAuras.myGUID then\n    scheduleReport(auraId, channel)\n  end\n  return request(auraId, channel)\nend\n\n\nfunction aura_env.CHAT_MSG_RAID(text, _, _, _, _, _, _, _, _, _, _, guid, ...)\n  return chatMessage(text, guid, \"RAID\")\nend\n\n\nfunction aura_env.CHAT_MSG_RAID_LEADER(text, _, _, _, _, _, _, _, _, _, _, guid, ...)\n  return chatMessage(text, guid, \"RAID\")\nend\n\n\nfunction aura_env.CHAT_MSG_PARTY(text, _, _, _, _, _, _, _, _, _, _, guid, ...)\n  return chatMessage(text, guid, \"PARTY\")\nend\n\n\nfunction aura_env.CHAT_MSG_PARTY_LEADER(text, _, _, _, _, _, _, _, _, _, _, guid, ...)\n  return chatMessage(text, guid, \"PARTY\")\nend\n\n\nfunction aura_env.CHAT_MSG_GUILD(text, _, _, _, _, _, _, _, _, _, _, guid, ...)\n  return chatMessage(text, guid, \"GUILD\")\nend\n\n\nfunction aura_env.OPTIONS()\n  return false\nend\n\n\nC_ChatInfo.RegisterAddonMessagePrefix(MESSAGE_PREFIX)",
